 ('223', '223', 'en_us', 'Resume', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<h4><strong>Objective</strong></h4>\n\n<p>Acquire a challenging and rewarding front–end web development position within a reputable organization where my skills are utilized collaboratively on deadline–driven team–oriented projects, contributing to solid company growth while bringing clients interactive needs to reality!</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<hr />', '<h4>Technical Skills</h4>\n\n<p>Strong leader with impeccable communication skills and refined ability to manage time and budget constraints competently for team oriented projects. Has an analytical approach to problem solving and reputable history making responsible decisions while working diligently towards meeting project goals and deadlines. An extremely detail-oriented developer.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Stack - HTML5, CSS2/3, LESS/SASS/SCSS/OOCSS, JavaScript/jQuery, AJAX/JSON, XML, XSL, XSLT, ASP.NET  </li><li>Tools - Experienced with multiple IDE\'s including Visual Studio 2013, MS Office 365/Exchange, MS Project, Adobe CS6, Atom, SublimeText3, Notepad++, TopStyle5, GIT, NodeJS, NPM, Grunt, Gulp, Bower, (modern web UNIX environment).</li><li>OOP - ASP.NET C#, OO JavaScript, PHP, OOCSS</li><li>Platforms - Windows XP+, Mac OSX, iOS</li></ul><hr />', '<h4><strong>Professional Experience</strong></h4>\n\n<ul><li>NASCAR, Charlotte, NC</li><li>Web Developer - NASCAR Digital Media, May 2015 - Present    <a href=\"http://www.nascar.com\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"{asset:224:url}\" alt=\"nascarLogo.png#asset:224\" title=\"nascarLogo.png#asset:224\" /></a></li></ul><ul><li>Developing applications that consume the data from 43 race cars that are traveling around a track at 200+mph</li><li>Create full-blown content rich web applications which inspire fan engagement throughout all levels of the sport.</li></ul>', '<h4><strong>Awards</strong></h4>\n\n<p>BFG Communications</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Client/Brand: Coca-Cola - Mello Yello</li><li>Award: IAC \"Best Beverage Website\"</li><li>Role: Front-end Web Developer</li></ul><hr />', '<h4><strong>Education</strong></h4>\n\n<p>The Art Institute of Pittsburgh</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Degree: Associates of Science - Web Design and Interactive Media</li><li>Honors Graduate: Dean\'s Award 2011 CGPA: 3.99</li><li>2010 John T. Barclay Memorial Scholarship Recipient - 1st Place</li></ul><p>American Public University</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Degree: Bachelors of Science – Information Technology .NET Concentration</li><li>2012 - Present<strong class=\"redactor-inline-converted\"> CGPA 4.00/4.00</strong></li></ul><hr />', '<p>* Letters of reference always provided upon request</p>', '<ul><li>BFG Communications, Hilton Head Island, SC</li><li>Front-end Web Developer - August 2012 - November 2014<a href=\"http://bfgcom.com\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"{asset:237:url}\" alt=\"bfg_logo.png#asset:237\" title=\"bfg_logo.png#asset:237\" /></a></li></ul><ul><li>Front-end web development on large scale deadline-driven enterprise websites working with a multi-disciplinary team of designers, project managers and account executives.</li><li>Mobile website development - produce responsive ASP.NET pages that render consistently across ALL major platforms, browsers and devices when supported.</li><li>Develop the engines that drive amazingly successful websites for several Fortune500 brands.</li><li>Responsive Email Development - Create, thoroughly test and deploy a library of mobile optimized responsive email templates, which render consistently across ALL major clients and supported devices.</li><li>Manage time and workflow on multiple creative projects while developing error free web sites and emails that meet W3C Recommendations and Standards.</li></ul><hr /><p><br /></p>', '<p>Jumpstreet Web Design/Development, Hiawassee, GA</p><p>Web Designer/Developer - June 2006 - August 2012</p><ul><li>Concept design, server administration and scripting; hand coding all approved creative documents using modern scripting and programming techniques, which meet W3C standards of compliancy and strong adherence to accessibility guidelines. Expert level of experience using HTML &amp; CSS</li><li>Construct and manage concept drawings for team members and clients employing flow charts, storyboards, wireframes and style guides using static and/or interactive mockups of all site pages.</li><li>Create models and prototypes, which establish user interface design, CSS based layouts and color palette schemes using corporate approved design documentation.</li><li>Develop Sitemaps, application models and page templates that meet project goals, user needs and industry standards.</li><li>Utilize HTML5 and CSS3 when supported using Modernizer for feature detection</li><li>Maintain high level of understanding in new technologies, W3C Compliance, Accessibility Guidelines and White Hat SEO methods.</li><li>Integrate technical considerations such as budgets, web design plan and equipment or performance requirements with strict adherence to legalities covering privacy and accessibility.</li><li>Create structured file/folder server directories enabling organized and efficient loading of all pages.</li><li>Assign various tasks to project personnel throughout programming and implementation stages of project</li><li>Proficient user of jQuery library allowing successful manipulation of the Document Object Model</li><li>Evaluate code making sure it is valid, properly structured, compatible and meets industry standards while rendering consistently across all major browsers and platforms.</li><li>Implement testing procedures utilizing various mainstream software applications and browsers in order to identify problems and correct issues or refer to appropriate personnel for correction while documenting all test plans and procedures employed</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><br /></p>', '2016-06-08 14:47:21', '2016-06-10 15:43:34', 'b24bd255-21b0-45d8-bc0a-329f9cc0cd62'),
